<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com">
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Space+Grotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500;600&display=swap">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/marketing.css">
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav class="nav">
      <div class="nav-inner shell">
        <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="bughq home">
          <span class="brand-mark">b</span>
          <span class="brand-name">bughq</span>
        </a>
        <div class="nav-links" aria-label="Primary navigation">
            <a href="/#features">Features</a>
            <a href="/use-cases">Use cases</a>
            <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
            <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/stacksjs/bughq">GitHub</a>
        </div>
        <a class="nav-login" href="/login">Log in</a>
        <a class="btn primary sm nav-cta" href="/register">Sign up</a>
        <details class="nav-menu">
          <summary aria-label="Open menu"><span class="burger" aria-hidden="true"></span></summary>
          <div class="nav-menu-panel">
            <a href="/#features">Features</a>
            <a href="/use-cases">Use cases</a>
            <a href="/pricing">Pricing</a>
            <a href="/docs">Docs</a>
            <a href="https://github.com/stacksjs/bughq">GitHub</a>
            <a href="/login">Log in</a>
            <a class="btn primary sm" href="/register">Sign up</a>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </nav>

    <main>
      <nav class="subnav shell" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <a href="/#features">Features</a><span class="sep">/</span>
        <span>Alerts and triage</span>
      </nav>

      <section class="feat-hero shell">
        <span class="kicker">Alerts</span>
        <h1>Get told when it matters, not for everything.</h1>
        <p>A brand new issue or a sudden spike reaches you where you already work. A known, quiet error stays quiet. You tune the threshold instead of muting the whole feed.</p>
        <div class="hero-actions">
          <a class="btn primary" href="/register">Get started</a>
          <a class="btn ghost" href="/docs">Read the docs</a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section shell reveal" aria-label="Alerts and triage preview">
        <div class="panel" style="max-width: 640px">
          <div class="panel-head"><span class="chart-cap">This week, by alert reason</span><span class="panel-tag">Sample data</span></div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">New issue</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 22%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">9</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Spike over baseline</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 12%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">5</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Regression after deploy</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 7%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">3</span>
          </div>
          <div class="bar-row">
            <span class="bar-label">Muted and known</span>
            <span class="bar-track"><span class="bar-fill" style="width: 100%"></span></span>
            <span class="bar-value">41</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section shell reveal" aria-labelledby="how-heading">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="how-heading" class="section-title">How it works</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="flow">
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">01</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Watch for what is new</h3>
              <p>A first-seen issue triggers an alert, because a new failure mode is the thing worth interrupting for.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">02</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Catch sudden spikes</h3>
              <p>When an existing issue jumps well above its baseline, that counts as news even if it is not new.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="flow-step">
            <span class="flow-num">03</span>
            <div>
              <h3>Reach your channel</h3>
              <p>Alerts land where your team already looks, so nobody has to camp on a dashboard.</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section shell reveal" aria-label="What you get">
        <div class="metrics">
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">New-issue alerts</div>
            <div class="m-label">Interrupt for a genuinely new failure, not a familiar one.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">Spike detection</div>
            <div class="m-label">A jump above baseline is treated as news.</div>
          </div>
          <div class="metric">
            <div class="m-value">Your channel</div>
            <div class="m-label">Delivered where the team already works.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section shell reveal" aria-labelledby="related-heading">
        <div class="section-head">
          <h2 id="related-heading" class="section-title">Pairs well with</h2>
        </div>
        <div class="related">
          <a href="/features/grouping">
            <div class="r-name">Fingerprint grouping</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Alerts fire on issues, not raw noise.</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/features/releases">
            <div class="r-name">Releases and environments</div>
            <div class="r-desc">Alert when a specific deploy regresses.</div>
          </a>
          <a href="/features/capture">
            <div class="r-name">Automatic capture</div>
            <div class="r-desc">The stream alerts are drawn from.</div>
          </a>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="section shell reveal" aria-label="Get started">
        <div class="cta-band">
          <h2>Ship with a net under you.</h2>
          <div class="cta-actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/register">Get started</a>
            <a class="btn ghost" href="/docs">Read the docs</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </section>
    </main>

    <footer class="footer shell">
      <div class="footer-bottom" style="border-top: none">
        <a class="brand" href="/" aria-label="bughq home">
          <span class="brand-mark">b</span>
          <span class="brand-name">bughq</span>
        </a>
        <span>Open source error tracking, built on Stacks and Postgres.</span>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
